The paper presents a computer algorithm for detecting solar photovoltaic arrays in high resolution aerial imagery using color information. This involves image processing and computer vision techniques, which are typically covered in the computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The algorithm also involves machine learning, which is covered in the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also discusses the potential for scalability and efficiency, which are covered in the distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the detection of objects in images, which is covered in the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
